race.comment: RICH MINX (3) is a leader who went close here first up and then raced favourite again at Ipswich, just nudged out. Has the rail and 3kg claim in easier and will be tough to beat. SPIRIT OF BRODIE (4) resumes for Adam Campton having switched barns. He's proven fresh and has been racing in stronger. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and keep onside. I AM VOODOO (1) has an inside gate and 3kg claim and would be a hope if he held his form from the latest. SHIPPING LANE (9) won well two back to shed the maiden tag before getting further back last start and closing well, finishing 0.9L off the winner. Can sit a touch closer today with Lerena replacing the apprentice hoop and he rates highly.
